        <heading>3298.  Hearing; order</heading>
        <content>
          <p>Art. 3298.  Hearing; order
If no opposition should be made within the time, the judge may grant to the administrator or executor the authority applied for, after the debt is proven, but if opposition should be made, he shall hear the matter and determine thereon in a summary manner.</p>
        </content>
